00006 static std::string unparseArmRegister(SgAsmArmRegisterReferenceExpression *reg) {
00007     const RegisterDescriptor &rdesc = reg->get_descriptor();
00008     const RegisterDictionary *dict = RegisterDictionary::dictionary_arm7();
00009     
00010     std::string name = dict->lookup(rdesc);
00011     if (name.empty()) {
00012         std::cerr <<"unparseArmRegister(" <<rdesc <<"): register descriptor not found in dictionary.\n";
00013         // std::cerr <<dict;
00014         ROSE_ASSERT(!"register descriptor not found in dictionary");
00015     }
00016 
00017     /* Add mask letters to program status registers */
00018     if (rdesc.get_major()==arm_regclass_psr && reg->get_psr_mask()!=0) {
00019         name += "_";
00020         if (reg->get_psr_mask() & 1) name += "c";
00021         if (reg->get_psr_mask() & 2) name += "x";
00022         if (reg->get_psr_mask() & 4) name += "s";
00023         if (reg->get_psr_mask() & 8) name += "f";
00024     }
00025 
00026     return name;
00027 }

00041 static std::string unparseArmSign(ArmSignForExpressionUnparsing sign) {
00042   switch (sign) {
00043     case arm_sign_none: return "";
00044     case arm_sign_plus: return "+";
00045     case arm_sign_minus: return "-";
00046 
00047     default:
00048       {
00049         ROSE_ASSERT (false);
00050         // DQ (11/28/2009): MSVC warns about a path that does not have a return stmt.
00051         return "error in unparseArmSign";
00052       }
00053   }
00054 }

00056 /* Helper function for unparseArmExpression(SgAsmExpression*)
00057  * 
00058  * If this function is called for an EXPR node that cannot appear at the top of an ARM instruction operand tree then the node
00059  * might create two strings: the primary expression return value and an additional string returned through the SUFFIX
00060  * argument. What to do with the additional string depends on layers higher up in the call stack.
00061  * 
00062  * The sign will be prepended to the result if EXPR is a value expression of some sort. */
00063 static std::string unparseArmExpression(SgAsmExpression* expr, const AsmUnparser::LabelMap *labels,
00064                                         ArmSignForExpressionUnparsing sign, std::string *suffix=NULL)
00065 {
00066     std::string result, extra;
00067     if (!isSgAsmValueExpression(expr)) {
00068         result += unparseArmSign(sign);
00069     }
00070     switch (expr->variantT()) {
00071         case V_SgAsmBinaryMultiply:
00072             ROSE_ASSERT (isSgAsmByteValueExpression(isSgAsmBinaryExpression(expr)->get_rhs()));
00073             result = unparseArmExpression(isSgAsmBinaryExpression(expr)->get_lhs(), labels, arm_sign_none) + "*" +
00074                      StringUtility::numberToString(isSgAsmByteValueExpression(isSgAsmBinaryExpression(expr)->get_rhs()));
00075             break;
00076         case V_SgAsmBinaryLsl:
00077             result = unparseArmExpression(isSgAsmBinaryExpression(expr)->get_lhs(), labels, arm_sign_none) + ", lsl " +
00078                      unparseArmExpression(isSgAsmBinaryExpression(expr)->get_rhs(), labels, arm_sign_none);
00079             break;
00080         case V_SgAsmBinaryLsr:
00081             result = unparseArmExpression(isSgAsmBinaryExpression(expr)->get_lhs(), labels, arm_sign_none) + ", lsr " +
00082                      unparseArmExpression(isSgAsmBinaryExpression(expr)->get_rhs(), labels, arm_sign_none);
00083             break;
00084         case V_SgAsmBinaryAsr:
00085             result = unparseArmExpression(isSgAsmBinaryExpression(expr)->get_lhs(), labels, arm_sign_none) + ", asr " +
00086                      unparseArmExpression(isSgAsmBinaryExpression(expr)->get_rhs(), labels, arm_sign_none);
00087             break;
00088         case V_SgAsmBinaryRor:
00089             result = unparseArmExpression(isSgAsmBinaryExpression(expr)->get_lhs(), labels, arm_sign_none) + ", ror " +
00090                      unparseArmExpression(isSgAsmBinaryExpression(expr)->get_rhs(), labels, arm_sign_none);
00091             break;
00092         case V_SgAsmUnaryRrx:
00093             result = unparseArmExpression(isSgAsmUnaryExpression(expr)->get_operand(), labels, arm_sign_none) + ", rrx";
00094             break;
00095         case V_SgAsmUnaryArmSpecialRegisterList:
00096             result += unparseArmExpression(isSgAsmUnaryExpression(expr)->get_operand(), labels, arm_sign_none) + "^";
00097             break;
00098         case V_SgAsmExprListExp: {
00099             SgAsmExprListExp* el = isSgAsmExprListExp(expr);
00100             const std::vector<SgAsmExpression*>& exprs = el->get_expressions();
00101             result += "{";
00102             for (size_t i = 0; i < exprs.size(); ++i) {
00103                 if (i != 0) result += ", ";
00104                 result += unparseArmExpression(exprs[i], labels, arm_sign_none);
00105             }
00106             result += "}";
00107             break;
00108         }
00109 
00110 
00111         case V_SgAsmBinaryAdd: {
00112             /* This node cannot appear at the top of an ARM instruction operand tree */
00113             SgAsmBinaryExpression *e = isSgAsmBinaryExpression(expr);
00114             result += unparseArmExpression(e->get_lhs(), labels, arm_sign_none) + ", " +
00115                       unparseArmExpression(e->get_rhs(), labels, arm_sign_plus);
00116             break;
00117         }
00118 
00119         case V_SgAsmBinarySubtract: {
00120             /* This node cannot appear at the top of an ARM instruction operand tree */
00121             SgAsmBinaryExpression *e = isSgAsmBinaryExpression(expr);
00122             result += unparseArmExpression(e->get_lhs(), labels, arm_sign_none) + ", " +
00123                       unparseArmExpression(e->get_rhs(), labels, arm_sign_minus);
00124             break;
00125         }
00126 
00127         case V_SgAsmBinaryAddPreupdate: {
00128             /* This node cannot appear at the top of an ARM instruction operand tree */
00129             SgAsmBinaryExpression *e = isSgAsmBinaryExpression(expr);
00130             result += unparseArmExpression(e->get_lhs(), labels, arm_sign_none) + ", " +
00131                       unparseArmExpression(e->get_rhs(), labels, arm_sign_plus);
00132             extra = "!";
00133             break;
00134         }
00135             
00136         case V_SgAsmBinarySubtractPreupdate: {
00137             /* This node cannot appear at the top of an ARM instruction operand tree */
00138             SgAsmBinaryExpression *e = isSgAsmBinaryExpression(expr);
00139             result += unparseArmExpression(e->get_lhs(), labels, arm_sign_none) + ", " +
00140                       unparseArmExpression(e->get_rhs(), labels, arm_sign_minus);
00141             extra = "!";
00142             break;
00143         }
00144 
00145         case V_SgAsmBinaryAddPostupdate: {
00146             /* Two styles of syntax depending on whether this is at top-level or inside a memory reference expression. */
00147             SgAsmBinaryExpression *e = isSgAsmBinaryExpression(expr);
00148             if (suffix) {
00149                 result += unparseArmExpression(e->get_lhs(), labels, arm_sign_none);
00150                 extra = ", " + unparseArmExpression(e->get_rhs(), labels, arm_sign_plus);
00151             } else {
00152                 /* Used by LDM* and STM* instructions outside memory reference expressions. RHS is unused. */
00153                 result = unparseArmExpression(e->get_lhs(), labels, arm_sign_none) + "!";
00154             }
00155             break;
00156         }
00157             
00158         case V_SgAsmBinarySubtractPostupdate: {
00159             /* Two styles of syntax depending on whether this is at top-level or inside a memory reference expression. */
00160             SgAsmBinaryExpression *e = isSgAsmBinaryExpression(expr);
00161             if (suffix) {
00162                 result += unparseArmExpression(e->get_lhs(), labels, arm_sign_none);
00163                 extra = ", " + unparseArmExpression(e->get_rhs(), labels, arm_sign_minus);
00164             } else {
00165                 /* Used by LDM* and STM* instructions outside memory reference expressions. RHS is unused. */
00166                 result += unparseArmExpression(e->get_lhs(), labels, arm_sign_none) + "!";
00167             }
00168             break;
00169         }
00170 
00171         case V_SgAsmMemoryReferenceExpression: {
00172             SgAsmMemoryReferenceExpression* mr = isSgAsmMemoryReferenceExpression(expr);
00173             SgAsmExpression* addr = mr->get_address();
00174             switch (addr->variantT()) {
00175                 case V_SgAsmRegisterReferenceExpression:
00176                 case V_SgAsmBinaryAdd:
00177                 case V_SgAsmBinarySubtract:
00178                 case V_SgAsmBinaryAddPreupdate:
00179                 case V_SgAsmBinarySubtractPreupdate:
00180                 case V_SgAsmBinaryAddPostupdate:
00181                 case V_SgAsmBinarySubtractPostupdate:
00182                     break;
00183                 default: ROSE_ASSERT (!"Bad addressing mode");
00184             }
00185 
00186             std::string suffix;
00187             result += "[" + unparseArmExpression(addr, labels, arm_sign_none, &suffix) + "]";
00188             result += suffix;
00189             break;
00190         }
00191 
00192         case V_SgAsmArmRegisterReferenceExpression:
00193             result += unparseArmRegister(isSgAsmArmRegisterReferenceExpression(expr));
00194             break;
00195         case V_SgAsmByteValueExpression:
00196         case V_SgAsmWordValueExpression:
00197         case V_SgAsmDoubleWordValueExpression: {
00198             SgAsmValueExpression *ve = isSgAsmValueExpression(expr);
00199             assert(ve!=NULL);
00200             uint64_t v = SageInterface::getAsmConstant(ve);
00201             result += "#" + unparseArmSign(sign) + StringUtility::numberToString(v);
00202             if (labels && v!=0) {
00203                 AsmUnparser::LabelMap::const_iterator li=labels->find(v);
00204                 if (li!=labels->end())
00205                     result += "<" + li->second + ">";
00206             }
00207             break;
00208         }
00209 
00210         default: {
00211             std::cerr << "Unhandled expression kind " << expr->class_name() << std::endl;
00212             ROSE_ASSERT (false);
00213         }
00214     }
00215 
00216     /* The extra data should be passed back up the call stack so it can be inserted into the ultimate return string. We can't
00217      * insert it here because the string can't be generated strictly left-to-right. If "suffix" is the null pointer then the
00218      * caller isn't expecting a suffix and we'll have to just do our best -- the result will not be valid ARM assembly. */
00219     if (extra.size()>0 && !suffix)
00220         result = "\"" + result + "\" and \"" + extra + "\"";
00221     if (suffix)
00222         *suffix = extra;
00223 
00224     if (expr->get_replacement() != "") {
00225         result += " <" + expr->get_replacement() + ">";
00226     }
00227     return result;
00228 }

00231 std::string unparseArmMnemonic(SgAsmArmInstruction *insn) {
00232     ROSE_ASSERT(insn!=NULL);
00233     std::string result = insn->get_mnemonic();
00234     std::string cond = unparseArmCondition(insn->get_condition());
00235     ROSE_ASSERT (insn->get_positionOfConditionInMnemonic() >= 0);
00236     ROSE_ASSERT ((size_t)insn->get_positionOfConditionInMnemonic() <= result.size());
00237     result.insert(result.begin() + insn->get_positionOfConditionInMnemonic(), cond.begin(), cond.end());
00238     return result;
00239 }

00242 std::string unparseArmExpression(SgAsmExpression *expr, const AsmUnparser::LabelMap *labels) {
00243     /* Find the instruction with which this expression is associated. */
00244     SgAsmArmInstruction *insn = NULL;
00245     for (SgNode *node=expr; !insn && node; node=node->get_parent()) {
00246         insn = isSgAsmArmInstruction(node);
00247     }
00248     ROSE_ASSERT(insn!=NULL);
00249 
00250     if (insn->get_kind() == arm_b || insn->get_kind() == arm_bl) {
00251         ROSE_ASSERT(insn->get_operandList()->get_operands().size()==1);
00252         ROSE_ASSERT(insn->get_operandList()->get_operands()[0]==expr);
00253         SgAsmDoubleWordValueExpression* tgt = isSgAsmDoubleWordValueExpression(expr);
00254         ROSE_ASSERT(tgt);
00255         return StringUtility::intToHex(tgt->get_value());
00256     } else {
00257         return unparseArmExpression(expr, labels, arm_sign_none);
00258     }
00259 }
